\tan\theta=y/x
r^{2}=x^{2}+y^{2}
\dot{x}=\frac{d}{dt}(r\cos\theta)=\frac{dr}{dt}\cos\theta-r\sin\theta\frac{d\theta}{dt}=\dot{r}\cos\theta-r\dot{\theta}\sin\theta
 x=r\cos\theta,\ y=r\sin\theta, 
 \dot{r}=r-r^3,\quad \dot{\theta}=1-\cos\theta. 
